fr.beaftech.collique

Class SingleElementList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.beaftech.collique.SingleElementCollection<E>
      • fr.beaftech.collique.SingleElementList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the element to store
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class SingleElementList<E>
extends SingleElementCollection<E>
implements java.util.List<E>
    Single element implementation of List. Permits all elements, including null and implements all optional collection operations with some restriction to add(Object) and SingleElementCollection.addAll(java.util.Collection) that will throw an UnsupportedOperationException when trying to add a second element to the list, thus because the list can only contain one element.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Arnould Guidat
